MODULE: src/bot
FILES: 8 (+32 command handlers in commands/handlers/)
RESPONSIBILITY: Telegram bot — message handling, command routing, file delivery, streaming output
INTERFACES:
- createTelegramBot(): Promise<Telegraf> — initialize bot with all command handlers and services
- bot._f018.subscribeCrossChannel(chatId): void — subscribe realtimeHub for cross-channel push
KEY_FILES:
- telegram.js: Main bot setup, text handler, file handling, stream publisher (~1080 lines)
- commands/index.js: Command registry and routing
- commands/help.js: Help text generation
- commands/handlers/output.js: F-020 /output [N] command — view recent AI CLI output history
- commands/handlers/cli.js: F-021 /cli command — backend switcher + profile manager
DEPENDENCIES:
- uses: telegraf: Telegram bot framework
- imports: src/services/ai-cli-service.js: executeAiCli, interruptAiCli, isAiCliRunning, restartAiCli
- imports: src/services/message-router.js: F-018 unified message routing
- imports: src/services/session-bind.js: F-018 session binding for cross-channel
- imports: src/services/realtime-hub.js: F-018 event subscription for cross-channel push
- imports: src/services/session-store.js: session state
- imports: src/services/chat-service.js: legacy (still imported for /reset command)
- imports: src/services/profile-store.js: F-021 CLI profile persistence singleton
- imports: src/services/backend-registry.js: F-021 backend registration at startup
- imports: src/utils/ansi-adapter.js: F-020 processChunk — strips ANSI before Telegram display
- imports: src/utils/output-segmenter.js: F-020 segmentOutput — logical boundary splitting
- imports: src/bot/commands/handlers/output.js: F-020 /output command + outputHistoryService singleton
TRAPS:
- Telegram bot text handler uses messageRouter.processMessage() (F-018) — no longer calls executeAiCli directly
- Cross-channel push only subscribes for bindings that exist at bot startup; dynamic bindings via API need manual subscribeCrossChannel() call
- Heartbeat progress messages disabled after F-018 migration to messageRouter (messageRouter lacks onHeartbeat hook)
- bot._f018 is an internal namespace — not a stable public API
- onAssistantChunk wraps chunk with ansiProcessChunk() (F-020) before pushing to streamPublisher — raw ANSI bytes from stdout are never forwarded to Telegram
- segmentOutput() replaces splitMessage() in render() inside createEditableStreamPublisher — ONLY in streaming path; cross-channel push (subscribeCrossChannel) still uses splitMessage()
- STREAM_MIN_CHARS (220) and STREAM_FLUSH_INTERVAL_MS (1200) are preserved unchanged — segmentation only changes where cuts happen, not how often
- outputHistoryService singleton exported from output.js — telegram.js imports it; tests must inject mock via handlerCtx to avoid mutating shared singleton state
- F-021 startup block calls profileStore.init({persistencePath}) then seeds default 'default' profile; must run before registerPipelineCommands() to ensure backendRegistry has profiles when handlers initialize
UPDATED: 2026-03-23
